This product is designed to build on, and interoperate with, the following
open-source projects (not vendored here; installed as dependencies or used as
external oracles):

  * Newton physics engine — Apache-2.0 (NVIDIA / Google DeepMind / Disney
    Research; Linux Foundation). https://github.com/newton-physics/newton
    NOTE: lumen/newton/vbd_fork.py is a derivative of Newton's SolverVBD
    (newton/_src/solvers/vbd/solver_vbd.py, Apache-2.0), modified to inject the
    tube-intrinsic contact barrier into the per-color AVBD solve. Original
    copyright (c) 2025 The Newton Developers; modifications (c) 2026 Seldinger.
  * NVIDIA Warp — Apache-2.0. https://github.com/NVIDIA/warp
  * STARK / SymX — accurate-tier oracle (cross-validation only).
  * ppf-contact-solver — GPU accurate-tier baseline (cross-validation only).
  * DiffDRR — differentiable X-ray rendering (sensor layer).

This repository deliberately does NOT depend on or derive from CathSim
(CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0) or any patient-derived data. See tools/check_firewall.py.
